sentences: Anselmo Sacasas (23 November 1912 – 22 January 1998) was a Cuban jazz pianist, bandleader, composer, and arranger.
He began to learn piano at the age of 6 from a female cousin, and 10 years later graduated from the music conservatory in Manzanillo.
In the early 1930s he was a member of Tata Pereira's orchestra.
In 1936 he met the singer Miguelito Valdés, with whom he would work in the Orquesta de los Hermanos Castro.
In 1940, Sacasas left for New York, where after some difficulty he was able to found his own orchestra in 1941.

In 1959 he became the musical director of the hotel Fountainbleu in Miami and Club Ronde.
In 1963 he became the director of the cabaret Tropicoro for thirteen years, after which he retired to Miami, where he died in 1998.
